> If we had a penny for every time we saw a badly cooked steak we'd probably be
> millionaires. There are certain cardinal tips you have to follow for a perfect
> result: 1) Allow your steak to come up to room temperature before you cook it
> 2) Get your frying pan super hot before your steak goes in and 3) Make sure
> you rest the steak on a warm plate for a few mins after cooking before you
> cut into it.

== Rosemary Roasted Potatoes ==

First you need to take your @flank steak{4} out of the fridge to bring it up to
room temperature. Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees and boil @water{300%ml}
for later. Chop your @new potatoes{2} into small 2cm cubes. Lightly crush your
@black peppercorns{2} in a #pestle and mortar{}. If you don't have a pestle and
mortar put them between two sheets of foil/clingfilm and give them a little
whack with a #rolling pin{}.

Remove the @rosemary{4}(leaves removed from stalks and finely chopped) leaves
from the stalks and very finely chop. Put your potatoes on a #baking tray{},
sprinkle over the chopped rosemary leaves and drizzle over @olive oil{3%tbsp}.
Sprinkle over @salt{½%tsp} and a good grind of pepper. Give the baking tray a
good shake so the potatoes are evenly coated and cook on the top shelf of the
oven for ~{30%minutes} until crispy (shake occasionally).

Peel and very finely chop the @echalion shallot{1} and cut your @broccoli{2}
into florets.

== Broccoli ==

Put your broccoli florets on a #baking tray{}, add @olive oil{2%tbsp},
@salt{½%tsp} and a good grind of pepper and pop in the oven for
~{15%minutes} until slightly crispy.

== Steak ==

Once the steak has come to room temperature, season it with @salt{pinch}.
Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat with @oil{2%tbsp}. Once almost smoking
hot, lay the steak into the pan and press it down.

> Lay the steak away from your body to stop oil spitting at you.

Cook the steak for ~{2%minutes} on each side for medium rare or ~{3%minutes}
each side for medium. Only turn the steak once and rest on a warm #plate{}
once cooked.

> Cover the steak with tin foil to keep warm whilst you finish off the rest.

== Peppercorn Sauce ==

Once the steak is removed from the pan, turn the heat to medium low and add
@olive oil{4%tsp} to the pan along with the chopped shallot. After cooking for
~{2%minutes}, add the peppercorns. One minute later, add your 300ml of boiled
water and stir in the @beef stock pot{1}.

Bubble away for a few mins and once the sauce has reduced by half, take off the
heat and stir in the @creme fraiche{1}.

> For a decadent touch, add 2 tsp of butter at this point (if you have any).

Slice your steak diagonally into 1cm strips and serve with your homemade
peppercorn sauce, potatoes and broccoli.